title: Shooter gets 23 years to life for ambushing NYC police twice in 12 hours, wounding 2
description: A shooter who ambushed police in New York City twice in 12 hours, wounding two officers, has been sentenced to 23 years to life in prison

title: Synagogue president found stabbed to death outside home
description: Police in Detroit are looking for clues after they said the president of a synagogue was found stabbed to death outside her home.

title: Little light, no beds, not enough anesthesia: A view from Gaza's hospitals
description: Hospitals are nearing collapse as doctors work under the most trying conditions.

title: Woman who made fake cancer claims on social media must pay restitution
description: An Iowa woman who falsely claimed to have cancer will stay out of prison after a judge gave her probation and a suspended sentence

title: CEO of tech conference resigns amid backlash for statements over Israel-Hamas war
description: Paddy Cosgrave, the chief executive officer of a prominent European tech conference called Web Summit, resigned from his role on Saturday amid backlash for his public statements that suggested Israel was committing war crimes

title: Woman returns from vacation, finds Atlanta home demolished
description: A company mistakenly demolished a home she owned in Atlanta.

title: WATCH:  Voices inside Gaza
description: ABC News’ James Longman reports on the two million Gaza residents in the crossfire as Israel ramps up its war with Hamas.

title: Ex-MLB pitcher arrested in 2021 homicide: Police
description: Danny Serafini, a former MLB pitcher, and another suspect were arrested in connection with the 2021 shootings of a couple, police said.

title: Man United, England soccer great Bobby Charlton dies at 86
description: He died Saturday surrounded by his family.

title: Ex-officer sentenced to 15 to 40 years after guilty pleas in sex assault cases
description: He was initially accused last year of posing as an active officer to lure girls.

title: WATCH:  Trucks with humanitarian aid enter through Rafah border crossing
description: Video shows the moment the first trucks of humanitarian aid entered Gaza as the Rafah border crossing between Egypt and the Gaza Strip opened on Saturday.

title: Hurricane Norma takes aim at Mexico's Los Cabos resorts, as Tammy threatens islands in the Atlantic
description: Hurricane Norma is bearing down on the resorts of Los Cabos at the southern tip of Mexico’s Baja California Peninsula, while Hurricane Tammy is headed for the islands of the Lesser Antilles in the Atlantic

title: Chicago and police union reach tentative deal on 20% raise for officers
description: The city of Chicago and the union representing its rank-and-file police officers have reached a tentative agreement on a four-year contract that would provide about a 20% raise for officers

title: Maui County police find additional remains, raising Lahaina wildfire death toll to 99
description: The death toll for the deadliest U.S. wildfire in more than a century has increased by one, to 99, after Maui County police found additional remains in Lahaina
